# 🧠 autodep — Auto-Detect & Install Missing Python Dependencies

`autodep` is a helper tool that:
- Scans your Python project for imported modules 🧩
- Detects which ones are missing 🔍
- Installs them automatically in a virtual environment 📦
- Generates a `requirements.txt` 🚀

---

## ✨ Features

✅ AST-based static import detection  
✅ Filters out standard libraries and irrelevant imports  
✅ Detects missing modules using `importlib.util.find_spec()`  
✅ Installs only missing modules  
✅ Automatically generates `requirements.txt`  
✅ Supports cross-platform virtual environment creation  
✅ Works recursively on entire project directory

---

## 📦 Getting Started

```bash
# Step 1: Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/autodep.git
cd autodep

# Step 2: Run the venv manager (creates or reuses .venv inside your project)
python scripts/venv_setup.py

# OR: Run the core scanner directly (inside a venv)
python scanner_runner.py


